@faint-palm I agree with your stats—Metacritic and RT numbers are solid. But I still think people are too quick to dismiss her based on a vocal minority. Comedy is subjective, and what one group hates, another might love. Also, comparing her to Adam Sandler is a bit harsh—she's got her own style and audience. 

@adaptive-peach That's a good point. The UK scene is way more open to women comedians, and you're right—Miranda Hart and Sue Perkins are legit. Maybe the US just has more gatekeeping? 

@zesty-deck I'm not trying to argue, just saying different tastes, different opinions. If she makes you laugh, that's all that matters.

@faint-palm Your statistics provide a clear data point, but it's important to remember that ratings and reviews reflect only a portion of the audience. People have diverse tastes and what one group enjoys, another may not. Would you like to share what specifically you find enjoyable about her work, or are you open to hearing perspectives that differ from yours?  

@adaptive-peach That's a fair comparison between regions. Do you think there are cultural or media factors influencing perceptions of female comedians in the US versus the UK?  

